In addition to @pembo13's nginx config, I found there were many static references in the JS. This required multiple [sub_filter](http://nginx.org/en/docs/http/ngx_http_sub_module.html#sub_filter) directives to fix, which requires nginx 1.9.4. Unfortunately, at time of writing, the [nginx ppa](https://launchpad.net/~nginx/+archive/ubuntu/development) only has 1.9.3. I had to compile nginx myself, using the configure arguments [here](http://nginx.org/en/linux_packages.html#arguments).

```nginx
location /flower/ {
    rewrite /flower/(.*) /$1  break;

    sub_filter '="/' '="/flower/';
    sub_filter_last_modified on;
    sub_filter_once off;

    proxy_pass http://FLOWER_HOST:FLOWER_PORT;
    proxy_set_header Host $host;
    proxy_redirect off;
    proxy_http_version 1.1;
    proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;
    proxy_set_header Connection "upgrade";
}

location /flower/static/ {
    sub_filter '/api' '/flower/api';
    sub_filter "'/monitor" "'/flower/monitor";
    sub_filter "'/worker" "'/flower/worker";
    sub_filter "'/'" "'/flower/'";
    sub_filter "'/dashboard'" "'/flower/dashboard'";
    sub_filter '"/update-dashboard"' '"/flower/update-dashboard"';
    sub_filter_types application/javascript;
    sub_filter_last_modified on;
    sub_filter_once off;

    alias <VIRTUALENV_PATH>/python2.7/dist-packages/flower/static/;
    expires 30d;
}
```

