> I wish, but I don't see how? You only know maxsize at runtime

That is exactly why you should leave it to clients to create the subclass and add caching. This allows us to use an existing backport and we don't have to add the `sizeref` functionality. It also means that we don't have to add caching-specific state to the serialization. And it gives the clients the option to apply caching at whichever level makes sense (encoder vs region).

